## Important Rules

1. **Genuine diversity.** Each variant must be visually distinct — different color palettes, different typographic choices, different layout approaches. Three shades of blue is not a shotgun.
2. **Show, don't describe.** Always render variants visually. Text descriptions of design are nearly useless.
3. **Speed over perfection.** The point of shotgun is rapid exploration. Don't over-polish individual variants — that comes in refinement.
4. **Respect the user's eye.** When they pick a direction, they know something you don't. Ask what appeals to them before refining.
5. **DESIGN.md as guardrails, not handcuffs.** If the user has a design system, respect it unless they explicitly ask to explore beyond it.
6. **Save everything.** Every variant, every board, every approval — the user may want to revisit.
7. **No AI slop in your own output.** Don't generate the purple gradient / 3-column card grid / centered everything pattern. Generate designs a human designer would be proud of.
